  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "First, they developed the Flores-200 many-to-many multilingual dataset, which enables testing translation quality.",
    "Then, they employed a distillation-based sentence encoding method called LASER3 to mine web data to produce parallel datasets for low-resource languages.",
    "Multilingual Mixtures-of-Experts models were trained to high performance levels using a combination of mined data and a specified set of human-translated seed data.",
    "The final model, which was trained on twice as many languages as previous models, performed 40% better than the prior state-of-the-art on the Flores-101 dataset.",
    "They developed a library of toxic words for all 200 languages using a combination of automatic and human evaluations to identify and prevent potentially damaging translations that are hallucinated by the translation algorithms."
  ],
